model_explanation: in S1, the prosodic focus is on "ROB," meaning Sam gave bananas exclusively to Rob and not to anyone else. S2 is stating that Tom did not receive bananas. This is entailed by S1, since if only Rob got bananas, it follows that Tom did not.

in S1, the prosodic focus is on "TOM," meaning Sam gave grapes exclusively to Tom and no one else. S2 says that Tom didn't get oranges, which is consistent with S1's focus on grapes being the only thing Tom received. There is no contradiction.

in S1, the prosodic focus is on "oranges," meaning Sue received only oranges from Sam and nothing else. S2 contradicts that by stating that Sue also received apples. This directly contradicts the exclusivity implied in S1.

in S1, the prosodic focus is on "SUE," meaning only Sue received bananas and no one else did. S2 says that Rob didn’t receive bananas, which matches the entailment from S1, since only Sue was given bananas.

in S1, the prosodic focus is on "oranges," meaning the only thing Sam gave Tom were oranges and nothing else. S2 says that Tom didn’t receive bananas, which is entailed by the exclusivity implied by S1.
in S1, the prosodic focus is on "apples," meaning the only thing Sam gave Sue were apples. S2 states that Sue didn’t get oranges, which fits perfectly with this. No contradictions arise.
in S1, the prosodic focus is on "grapes," meaning Sue only got grapes and nothing else. S2 states that Sue didn’t get apples, which logically follows from S1’s exclusivity.
in S1, the prosodic focus is on "oranges," meaning Ellen received only oranges from Sam. S2 says Sam also gave Ellen bananas, which contradicts the exclusivity premise in S1.
in S1, the prosodic focus is on "grapes," meaning Mary only received grapes from Sam. S2 states that Mary didn’t get apples, which fits the entailment suggested by S1’s exclusivity.

in S1, the prosodic focus is on "BILL," meaning the only person who received oranges from Sam was Bill, and no one else. S2 says Mary also received oranges, which is independent of the restriction imposed on Bill. This doesn’t directly contradict or entail S1, but rather introduces an independent claim.
